-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Oando Nigeria, United Bank for Africa
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-02-08T15:21:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-oando-nigeria-united-bank-for-africa.html
The  Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share
Index  fell for a second day, weakening 0.5 percent to 20,693.84
at the close in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from
the bourse.  The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index  jumped 1.4 percent to
937.94, the first gain in three days in Windhoek. Kenya’s  All-
Share Index  climbed for a second day, increasing 0.2 percent to
54.64 in Nairobi, the highest close since Jan. 20. Mauritius’s
 SEMDEX Index  gained 0.3 percent to 1,833.5 by the end of
trading.  The following shares were active in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Oando Plc  (OANDO NL), a Nigerian  oil company , advanced for
a third day, rising 2.5 percent to 18.4 naira, the highest close
since Jan. 30. Oil rose to its highest in a week in  New York 
after a report showed U.S. stockpiles shrank, signaling
increased demand in the world’s biggest crude consumer.  United Bank for Africa Plc  (UBA NL), a Nigerian lender with
operations in 19 countries, weakened 0.5 percent, after earlier
declining the maximum daily limit of 5 percent, to close at 1.99
naira. The bank expects a loss for 2011, “driven principally by
one-off write-offs against earnings, including those arising
from the transfer of loans to the Asset Management Company of
 Nigeria ,” it said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
